name: Texas Aggie CattleWomen
description: The purpose of the Texas Aggie CattleWomen will be to educate the student body and the public about the beef industry. This includes holding and/or sponsoring events that promote beef, provide information on the beef industry, educate the student body and public on the nutritional value of beef, and explain the impact the beef industry has on our culture. Specific events include educational displays ("tailgates") at athletic events, local conventions on beef, and hosting and/or participating in competitions relative to the beef industry. TACW will also regularly meet with other members of the Texas CattleWomen (TCW) at their chapter meetings.
